🔷 ☕ Java 21 (2023) — Concurrency Revolution (LTS)

🚩 Problem before Java 21

Threads were:
-Heavy
-Expensive
-Needed thread pools
-Async programming (CompletableFuture) was complex


🔑 What Java 21 introduced

1. Virtual Threads (🔥 Core Feature)

Thread.startVirtualThread(() -> {
    callDatabase();
});

👉 Deep concept:

-JVM manages threads instead of OS
-Threads are paused/resumed efficiently

💡 Why it matters

Before:

1000 users → 1000 threads → heavy ❌

Now:

100,000 users → manageable ✅


2. Structured Concurrency (Preview)

👉 Treat multiple threads as one unit:

-If one fails → cancel all
-Easier error handling

3. Scoped Values

👉 Alternative to ThreadLocal

-Safer
-Works better with virtual threads

4. Pattern Matching (Fully Enhanced)

Even more powerful switch handling

🔄 Improvement over Java 17

👉 Java 17 improved code structure
👉 Java 21 improved system scalability

✅ Final Impact

👉 Java 21 made:
a. High-concurrency apps easier
b. Microservices more scalable